text: Sid Ali Lamri (born February 3, 1991 in Sétif) is an Algerian football player who plays for Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1 club CS Constantine. He plays primarily as a central midfielder. ==Club career== Born in Sétif, Lamri started his career in the youth ranks of his hometown club ES Sétif. In 2008, Lamri was a member of Sétif's under-17 team that won the Algerian U17 Cup, and followed that up two years later with the Algerian U20 Cup trophy with Setif's under-20 team. In 2014, Lamri played a key role in Sétif's 2014 CAF Champions League triumph, starting in first the leg of the final against AS Vita Club, which ended 2-2, and coming as a substitute in the return leg. ==Honours== ES Sétif * CAF Champions League (1): 2014 * CAF Super Cup: 2015 * Algerian Ligue 1 (2): 2014–15, 2016–17 CS Constantine * Algerian Ligue 1 (1): 2017–18 ==External links== * * ==References== Category:1991 births Category:Algerian footballers Category:Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1 players Category:ES Sétif players Category:MSP Batna players Category:Footballers from Sétif Category:Living people Category:CS Constantine players Category:Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 2 players Category:Association football midfielders
